# Target: the MiniMax-M3-MXFP8 fused QKV projection
# (`generic_fused_qkv_matmul_kv_cache_paged_ragged_scale_float4`, the dual-mode
# NVFP4/MXFP8 entry; op `mo.fused_qkv_matmul.ragged.paged.scale.mxfp8`). MXFP8:
# float8_e4m3fn input + weights, float8_e8m0fnu (E8M0) block scales over 32-elem
# K blocks in the rank-5 SF-atom layout, fp32 accum; computes hidden @ [Wq|Wk|Wv]^T,
# returns Q (bf16) and SCATTERS K/V into the paged cache. The ragged shape (batch,
# per-batch cache lengths driving the K/V scatter slot, per-batch new-token counts)
# is the runtime fuzz axis (M = total tokens); num_q_heads/num_kv_heads/hidden are
# compile-time (`-D g3_num_q_heads=.. -D g3_num_kv_heads=.. -D g3_hidden=..`,
# default 8/1/256; the tuned SM100 matmul reads N/K from the static shape);
# head_dim fixed at 128, every band a multiple of SF_MN_GROUP_SIZE=128.
# memory-safety primary (the K/V cache scatter is the OOB-write risk); `ref`
# (--check 1) is a host fp32-accum naive dequant GEMM (E8M0 block dequant), split
# into Q (vs output) + K/V (vs the cache read-back). B200-only (SM100 + static N/K).
mojo_test(
    name = "fuzz_fused_qkv_matmul_mxfp8.mojo.test",
